"{\"uid\": \"dailypost.ng-2024-02-27-2024-olympic-qualifier-why-i-benched-oshoala-against-cameroon\", \"text\": \"Published  on  By  Super Eagles head coach, Randy Waldrum has revealed the reason behind his decision to bench Asisat Oshoala in Monday's 2024 Olympic Games qualifier against the Indomitable Lionesses of Cameroon.  The reigning African women's Player of the Year was expected to start the game but Waldrum instead named Tenerife star, Esther Okoronkwo in the starting line-up.  Okoronkwo justified the gaffer's faith by netting the winning goal in the 14th minute.  Oshoala later replaced the forward in the second half.  When queried on his decision after the game, Waldrum said he named the best line-up for the game.  \\\"I think we put out what we thought was the best eleven for the day to start the match. But we are fully confident of every player, we had some players that did not get minutes but are fully capable of helping us,\\\" the American stated.  Super Eagles, Argentina friendly called off  Transfer: Whoever signed Mudryk should be sacked - Bent tells Chelsea  WAFCON 2026: Madugu drops Oshoala, lists 25 players for Cameroon friendlies  UCL play-off: Oshoala predicts Benfica vs Real Madrid clash  WAFCON 2026Q: Oshoala, Ijamilusi hit camp as Super Falcons begin preparation for Benin clash  Oshoala scoops Saudi Women's Premier League Player of the Month  Saudi League: Al-Hilal must sustain winning momentum - Oshoala  Transfer: Oshoala moves to Saudi club Al-Hilal  Copyright \\u00a9Daily Post Media Ltd\"}"